Certainly! Below is a LaTeX document that includes a limerick with the specified structure. You can copy this code into a `.tex` file and compile it using a LaTeX editor like Overleaf or TeXShop.

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{lipsum}

\begin{document}

\title{A Limerick}
\author{}
\date{}
\maketitle

\begin{verse}
There once was a \textbf{cat} from \textbf{Perth} \\
Whose \textbf{tail} was \textbf{long} and \textbf{mirth} \\
They \textbf{danced} \textbf{gracefully} all day \\
In a \textbf{garden} far away \\
Oh, how \textbf{amazing} was that \textbf{cat} from \textbf{Perth}!
\end{verse}

\end{document}
```

You can replace the placeholders (like `cat`, `Perth`, `tail`, etc.) with your own words to customize the limerick as you wish. Enjoy crafting your personalized poem!
